HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 625
By McKenzie
A RESOLUTION to commend Alex Nelson for exemplary service
as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, this body is pleased to recognize certain persons
who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the betterment of the legislative
process; and
WHEREAS, Alex Nelson is one such individual, who has distinguished himself in his role
as a legislative intern for Representative Sam McKenzie; Mr. Nelson's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators he assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, a student at the University of Tennessee at Martin (UT Martin), where he is
highly regarded by his peers, Alex Nelson has achieved academic success while majoring in
political science with a concentration in public administration and participating in numerous
extracurricular activities; and
WHEREAS, Alex Nelson hails from Memphis and is the middle of fraternal triplets, a
background that has shaped his strong sense of family, leadership, and perseverance; and
WHEREAS, since 2023, Mr. Nelson has been a proud member of the Kappa Omicron
Chapter of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Incorporated, which he currently serves as the 2nd vice
president, demonstrating his commitment to the fraternity's principles of Brotherhood,
Scholarship, and Service; he has had the distinct honor of representing the Southwestern
Region of Phi Beta Sigma Fraternity, Incorporated, on the front cover of Crescent magazine,
highlighting his leadership and dedication to the fraternity's mission; and
WHEREAS, additionally, he has served as a member of the Zeta Chi Chapter of Alpha
Kappa Psi Professional Business Fraternity since 2021, in furtherance of his professional
development and commitment to excellence in business leadership; and
WHEREAS, during his tenure at UT Martin, Mr. Nelson has earned a number of awards
and recognitions, including the University Service Award for his exceptional dedication to
